  "prompt": "Will a magnet stick to copper?",
  "response": "No, a regular magnet will **not** stick to copper.\n\nCopper is not a ferromagnetic material like iron, nickel, or cobalt. Ferromagnetic materials have unpaired electrons that align themselves parallel to each other, creating a strong magnetic field that interacts strongly with magnets.\n\nCopper is a **diamagnetic** material. Diamagnetic materials are weakly repelled by a magnetic field. This repulsion is very weak and not something you'd notice with a typical household magnet.\n\nHowever, under extremely strong magnetic fields, you can observe a slight repulsion in copper. But for all practical purposes, a magnet will not stick to copper.\n",
